[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man arrested over Glasgow pensioner death

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been arrested in connection with the fatal stabbing of an elderly man in Glasgow.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
John Baker, 76, died after being found in a street in the Bridgeton area, just after midnight in the early hours of Wednesday.
Police launched a murder inquiry and said the death may be connected with an earlier robbery and an attempted robbery.
The 24-year-old is expected to appear at Glasgow Sheriff Court on Monday.
Inquiries are continuing and a significant police presence remains within the Calton and Bridgeton areas.
